    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> For example, they might want to leverage the `insights` middleware to send events to third-party trackers, but not necessarily to Algolia directly. In that case `userToken` for Algolia is not needed, but they still want the middleware to work.\r\n\r\nSeeing the code, this means that they'll still see a warning when using the middleware with a non-Algolia analytics integration. Should we not rather explain (e.g., with a guide) how to create a middleware to plug their own analytics solution?",
    "created_at": "2021-04-07T10:07:19Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/4724#issuecomment-814787556",
    "id": 814787556,
